                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="429854" author="yujian" created="Tue, 1 Oct 2024 23:25:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &apos;-&apos; is actually replaced with &apos;_&apos; in&#160;LUSTRE-VERSION-GEN, which is called in configure.ac and run by autogen.sh.&lt;br/&gt;
I hit the illegal char error because I didn&apos;t run autogen.sh, so this is not a bug. Let&apos;s close this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="340217" author="yujian" created="Wed, 13 Jul 2022 04:57:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Oleg,&lt;br/&gt;
While updating LUSTRE-VERSION-GEN to create a new RC, could you please avoid using dash char &apos;-&apos; in DEFAULT_VERSION?&lt;br/&gt;
FYI, after I changed &apos;2.15.0-RC5&apos; to &apos;2.15.0_RC5&apos;, &apos;make rpms&apos; passed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
